In root directory of the project:

- Build the jar file with command on cli: gradle build -x test
- Check, if the given JRE string in the Dockerfile is the correct one. If not, update the JRE string.
- Copy Dockerfile to root directory.
- Execute command on cli:
    sudo docker build -t springboot/medmanagementapp:V0.0.6 .
    # sudo docker build --build-arg JAR_FILE=build/libs/\*.jar -t springboot/medmanagementapp:V0.0.6 .
- Check, whether image was build with: sudo docker image list


-----------
sudo docker exec -it medmanagement-db bash
mariadb -u root -p"<Password>"


-----------
mysql> CREATE USER 'root'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY '<PASSWORD>';
mysql> GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON *.* TO 'root'@'%' WITH GRANT OPTION;
mysql> FLUSH PRIVILEGES;


------------
Backup (from Prod)
sudo docker exec medmanagement_db mariadb-dump -u <user> -p"<Password>" medmanagementdb > ./medmanagementdb_XYZ.sql

Restore (to Dev)
// Copy backup file into the container
sudo docker cp ./medmanagementdb_XYZ.sql medmanagement-db:/medmanagementdb_XYZ.sql
// Read data into database
sudo docker exec medmanagement-db bash -c 'mariadb -u root -p"<password>" medmanagementdb_dev < ./medmanagementdb_XYZ.sql'